UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2278
1 AN ACT relating to data centers.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 61 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Data center" means a facility or group of facilities engaged in the primary
7 services of storing, managing, transporting, and processing digital data;
8 including but not limited to:
9 1. Computer and network systems, including associated components
10 such as servers, network equipment and appliances,
11 telecommunications systems, and data storage systems;
12 2. Systems for monitoring and managing infrastructure performance;
13 3. Internet-related equipment and services;
14 4. Data communications connections;
15 5. Environmental controls;
16 6. Cooling systems;
17 7. Power generation systems;
18 8. Auxiliary buildings;
19 9. Fire protection systems;
20 10. Security systems and services; and
21 11. Any supporting infrastructure;
22 (b) "Nondisclosure or confidentiality agreement" means an agreement or
23 contract that includes a provision or clause that prohibits a party from
24 disclosing, discussing, describing, or commenting on the agreement or its
25 terms beyond protections authorized by statute; and
26 (c) "Public agency" has the same meaning as in KRS 61.870.
27 (2) (a) A public agency shall not enter into a nondisclosure or confidentiality
Page 1 of 4
